-!- FUNCTION: Pump for glutathione S-conjugates. Mediates the
    transport of S-conjugates such as GSH, S-(2,4-dinitrophenyl)-
    glutathione (DNP-GS), GSSG, cyanidin 3-glucoside-GS (C3G-GS) and
    metolachlor-GS (MOC-GS), glucuronides such as 17-beta-estradiol
    17-(beta-D-glucuronide) (E(2)17betaG), and of the chlorophyll
    catabolite such as B.napus nonfluorescent chlorophyll catabolite
    (Bn-NCC-1).
-!- CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: ATP + H(2)O + xenobiotic(In) = ADP + phosphate
    + xenobiotic(Out).
-!- ENZYME REGULATION: Reciprocal promotion of DNP-GS and E(2)17betaG
    uptake. E(2)17betaG uptake is also stimulated by GSH and S-methyl-
    glutathione (S-methyl-GS), and, to a lower extent, by GSSG and
    C3G-GS. Metolachlor-GS and decyl-GS slightly inhibit E(2)17betaG
    uptake.
-!- BIOPHYSICOCHEMICAL PROPERTIES:
    Kinetic parameters:
      KM=750 uM for E(2)17betaG (at pH 8.0 and 25 degrees Celsius);
      KM=240 uM for E(2)17betaG (with 100 uM DNP-GS at pH 8.0 and 25
      degrees Celsius);
      KM=4.7 uM for E(2)17betaG (with 500 uM GSH at pH 8.0 and 25
      degrees Celsius);
      KM=66 uM for DNP-GS (at pH 8);
      KM=20 uM for DNP-GS (with 100 uM E(2)17betaG at pH 8 and 25
      degrees Celsius);
      KM=73 uM for GSSG (at pH 8);
      KM=75 uM for MOC-GS (at pH 8);
      KM=15 uM for Bn-NCC-1 (at pH 8);
      Vmax=8.8 nmol/min/mg enzyme with E(2)17betaG as substrate (at pH
      8.0 and 25 degrees Celsius);
      Vmax=11.5 nmol/min/mg enzyme with E(2)17betaG as substrate (with
      100 uM DNP-GS at pH 8.0 and 25 degrees Celsius);
      Vmax=33 nmol/min/mg enzyme with E(2)17betaG as substrate (with
      500 uM GSH at pH 8.0 and 25 degrees Celsius);
      Vmax=2 nmol/min/mg enzyme with DNP-GS as substrate (at pH 8 and
      25 degrees Celsius);
      Vmax=1.8 nmol/min/mg enzyme with DNP-GS as substrate (with 100
      uM E(2)17betaG at pH 8 and 25 degrees Celsius);
      Vmax=3.8 nmol/min/mg enzyme with GSSG as substrate (at pH 8);
      Vmax=13.6 nmol/min/mg enzyme with MOC-GS as substrate (at pH 8);
      Vmax=6.3 nmol/min/mg enzyme with Bn-NCC-1 as substrate (at pH
      8);
-!- SUBUNIT: Interacts with FKBP42/TWD1 and probably with calmodulin
    (CaM).
-!- SUBCELLULAR LOCATION: Vacuole; vacuolar membrane; multi-pass
    membrane protein (Potential). Note=Tonoplast.
-!- TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Ubiquitous, at low levels.
-!- INDUCTION: By 1-chloro-2,4-dinitrobenzene (CDNB).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the ABC transporter family. Conjugate
    transporter (TC 3.A.1.208) subfamily.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 2 ABC transmembrane type-1 domains.
-!- SIMILARITY: Contains 2 ABC transporter domains.
-!- CAUTION: Ref.2 (AAC04246) sequence differs from that shown due to
    frameshifts in positions 1212 and 1223.
-!- CAUTION: Ref.4 sequence differs from that shown due to frameshifts
    in positions 1223 and 1234.
-!- CAUTION: Ref.5 sequence differs from that shown due to a
    frameshift in position 1461.
